### Positioning in CSS
The positioning property specifies the type of positioning method used for an element. Element are positioned using the top, bottom, left and right values.

## Types of positioning
Static -> Elements are positioned static by default
Relative -> Positoned relative to its normal position.
Fixed -> Always stays int he same place even if the page is scrolled.
Sticky -> Positioned based on the user's scroll position.
Absolute -> Positioned relative to the nearest positioned ancestor.


## CSS float
The CSS float property specifies how an element should float and is used for positioning elements such as images or containers.

## Float properties
Property value          Datails
left                 Element floats to the left of its container
right                Element floats to the right of its container
inherit              The element inherits the float value of its parent
none                 The element does not float. Remains in default position.

